text: Is there a way to create a python object that will be not sortable?
Is there a possibility to create any python object that will be not sortable?
So that will be an exception when trying to sort a list of that objects?
I created a very simple class, didn't define any comparison methods, but still instances of this class are comparable and thus sortable.
Maybe, my class inherits comparison methods from somewhere.
But I don't want this behaviour.
